This paper is about using recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to model natural language and improve inference time through "neural speed reading". This topic is closely related to natural language processing (NLP), which falls under the computer science sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model that uses agents to skip and jump text during inference, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the model's performance in terms of accuracy and speed, which are common concerns in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of punctuation structure, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) for detecting and segmenting objects in images.
